  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6760 sitting between the negative gamma wall at 6750 (-11.9B) and positive gamma peak at 6775 (+10.1B), dealers are currently in neutral hedging mode but poised for aggressive buying if we break below 6750 or selling above 6775. The regime flip to PIN with massive GEX surge (395% 1-min change) suggests dealers just flipped to long gamma and will now provide stabilizing flow - selling any push toward 6775-6780 resistance and buying dips toward the 6750-6745 support cluster. Key inflection points are 6750 (where dealer buying accelerates) and 6775 (where dealer selling kicks in), creating a tight 25-point range with amplified volatility below and capping action above.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect choppy range-bound action between 6750-6775 with dealers fighting moves outside this zone.",
